The paper deals with the unsupervised task of finding repeated patterns or motifs in a time series, which is a common problem in data mining (cs.DM). The proposed approach uses a genetic algorithm, which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The algorithm is designed to be flexible and adaptable to different situations, which is a characteristic of many algorithms in the field of computational intelligence and soft computing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to different types of data, including traffic volume measurements, accelerometer signals, and telephone call records, which suggests a broad applicability of the method (cs.NE).
